 Is (Vikki Watson song)|Love Is]]\"\n| 49\n| 4th\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 1986|1986]]\n| [[Ryder (band)|Ryder]]\n| \"[[Runner in the Night]]\"\n| 98{{efn|name=Chart86/87|Both \"Runner In the Night\" and \"Only The Light\" reached the lower end of the top 100 of the singles chart reserved for new releases that were 'bubbling under' the official Top 75, but failed to register in the official top 75 itself.}}\n| 7th\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 1987|1987]]\n| [[Rikki (British singer)|Rikki]]\n| \"[[Only the Light]]\"\n| 96{{efn|name=Chart86/87}}\n| 13th\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 1988|1988]]\n| [[Scott Fitzgerald (singer)|Scott Fitzgerald]]\n| \"[[Go (Scott Fitzgerald song)|Go]]\"\n| 52\n| 2nd\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 1989|1989]]\n| [[Live Report]]\n| \"[[Why Do I Always Get it Wrong?]]\"\n| 73\n| 2nd\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 1990|1990]]\n| [[Emma (Welsh singer)|Emma]]\n| \"[[Give a Little Love Back to the World]]\"\n| 33\n| 6th\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 1991|1991]]\n| [[Samantha Janus]]\n| \"[[A Message to Your Heart]]\"\n| 30\n| 10th\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 1992|1992]]\n| [[Michael Ball (singer)|Michael Ball]]\n| \"[[One Step Out of Time]]\"\n| 20\n| 2nd\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 1993|1993]]\n| [[Sonia (singer)|Sonia]]\n| \"[[Better the Devil You Know (Sonia song)|Better the Devil You Know]]\"\n| 15\n| 2nd\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 1994|1994]]\n| [[Frances Ruffelle]]\n| \"[[Lonely Symphony (We Will Be Free)|We Will Be Free (Lonely Symphony)]]\"\n| 25\n| 10th\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 1995|1995]]\n| [[Love City Groove]]\n| \"[[Love City Groove (song)|Love