 (comedian)|Roy Walker]]\n|-\n| North England\n| [[Kelli Young]]\n|-\n| Midlands England\n| [[Rustie Lee]]\n|-\n| South East England\n| [[Alistair Appleton]]\n|-\n| South West England\n| Simon Grant\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n== Viewing figures ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:40%;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Nominal\n! Share\n! Channel\n|-\n| [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 2008|2008]]\n| 5,000,300<ref name=\"BARB\"/>\n| 24%<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2008/mar/03/tvratings.television1|title=Eurovision warm-up draws 5m|newspaper=The Guardian|date=3 March 2008|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n| rowspan=3|[[BBC One]]\n|-\n| [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 2009|2009]]\n| 5,610,000<ref name=\"BARB\">{{cite web|url=http://www.barb.co.uk/viewing-data/weekly-top-30/|title=Weekly Top 30 Programmes|publisher=Broadcasters' Audience Research Board|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n| 25%<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2009/feb/02/your-country-needs-you-watched-by-54m|title=Your Country Needs You show watched by 5.4m|newspaper=The Guardian|date=2 February 2009|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 2010|2010]]\n| 2,920,000<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digitalspy.com/tv/ratings/news/a208691/29m-see-dubovie-selected-for-eurovision/|title=2.9m see Dubovie selected for Eurovision|date=15 March 2010|website=Digital Spy|accessdate=12 February 2018}}</ref>\n| 12.5%\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" {{N/A|''Internal selections from [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 2011|2011]] to [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 2015|2015]]''}}\n|-\n| [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 2016|2016]]\n| 680,000<ref name=\"Viewing Figures 2016\u201317\">{{Cite news|url=https://eurovoix.com/2017/01/28/united-kingdom-eurovision-decide-viewing-figures-double-2016|title=United Kingdom: Eurovision: You Decide viewing figures double over 2016|last1=Granger|