und of voting to eliminate 4 of the 8 songs. This was televised in 1996 but switched to radio from 1997 to 2003.\n\n===Host(s) and venue===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Selection show\n! Venue\n! National final main host\n! National final co-host\n! Semi final/heat host\n|-\n| 1956\n| colspan=\"5\" {{n/a|UK did not participate}}\n|-\n| [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 1957|1957]]\n| ''Festival Of British Popular Songs''\n| [[Lyric Theatre (Hammersmith)|The King's Theatre Hammersmith]]\n| [[David Jacobs (broadcaster)|David Jacobs]]\n| {{n/a|No co-host}}\n| [[David Jacobs (broadcaster)|David Jacobs]]\n|-\n| 1958\n| colspan=\"5\" {{n/a|UK did not participate}}\n|-\n| [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 1959|1959]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''Eurovision Song Contest British Final''\n| rowspan=\"17\"|[[BBC Television Theatre]]\n| [[Pete Murray (disc jockey)|Pete Murray]]\n| rowspan=\"39\" {{n/a|No co-host}}\n| [[Pete Murray (disc jockey)|Pete Murray]]\n|-\n| [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 1960|1960]]\n| [[David Jacobs (broadcaster)|David Jacobs]]\n| [[David Jacobs (broadcaster)|David Jacobs]]\n|-\n| [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 1961|1961]]\n| rowspan=\"35\"| ''A Song For Europe'' \n| [[Katie Boyle]]\n| rowspan=\"35\" {{n/a|No semi final/heat}}\n|-\n| [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 1962|1962]]\n| rowspan=\"5\"|[[David Jacobs (broadcaster)|David Jacobs]]\n|-\n| [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 1963|1963]]\n|-\n| [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 1964|1964]]\n|-\n| [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 1965|1965]]\n|-\n| [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 1966|1966]]\n|-\n| [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 1967|1967]]\n| [[Rolf Harris]]\n|-\n| [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 1968|1968]]\n| [[Cilla Black]]\n|-\n| [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 1969|1969]]\n| [[Michael Aspel]]\n|-\n| [[United King