he Eurovision Song Contest 2009|2009]]\n| 5,610,000<ref name=\"BARB\">{{cite web|url=http://www.barb.co.uk/viewing-data/weekly-top-30/|title=Weekly Top 30 Programmes|publisher=Broadcasters' Audience Research Board|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n| 25%<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2009/feb/02/your-country-needs-you-watched-by-54m|title=Your Country Needs You show watched by 5.4m|newspaper=The Guardian|date=2 February 2009|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 2010|2010]]\n| 2,920,000<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digitalspy.com/tv/ratings/news/a208691/29m-see-dubovie-selected-for-eurovision/|title=2.9m see Dubovie selected for Eurovision|date=15 March 2010|website=Digital Spy|accessdate=12 February 2018}}</ref>\n| 12.5%\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" {{N/A|''Internal selections from [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 2011|2011]] to [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 2015|2015]]''}}\n|-\n| [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 2016|2016]]\n| 680,000<ref name=\"Viewing Figures 2016\u201317\">{{Cite news|url=https://eurovoix.com/2017/01/28/united-kingdom-eurovision-decide-viewing-figures-double-2016|title=United Kingdom: Eurovision: You Decide viewing figures double over 2016|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|publisher=Eurovoix|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n| 3.2%<ref name=\"Viewing Figures 2016\u201317\"/>\n| [[BBC Four]]<ref name=\"BBC Two\">{{Cite news|url=http://metro.co.uk/2017/01/23/eurovision-2017-heres-how-the-uk-will-be-choosing-its-entry-for-this-years-contest-6391607/|title=Eurovision 2017: Here\u2019s how the UK will be choosing its entry for this year\u2019s contest|last1=Westbrook|first1=Caroline|accessdate=22 October 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 2017|2017]]\n| 1,260,000<ref name=\"Viewing Figures 2016\u201317\"/>\n| 6.6%\n| rowspan=3|[[BBC Two]]<ref name=\"BBC Two\"/><ref name=\"BBC2 confirmed 2018\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2017-eurovision-you-decide|title=Brighton Dome to be home of Eurovision: You Decide 2018 on BBC Two!|website=bbc.co.uk|publisher=[[British Broadcasting Corporation]]|date=16 November 2017|accessdate=22 November 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 2018|2018]]\n| 900,000<ref name=\"Ratings 2018\"/>\n| 4.8%<ref name=\"Ratings 2018\">{{cite web|last=Granger|first=Andy|url=https://eurovoix.com/2018/02/08/united-kingdom-less-1-million-viewers-watched-eurovision-decide/|title=United Kingdom: Less Than 1 Million Viewers Watched Eurovision: You Decide|website=eurovoix.com|publisher=Eurovoix|date=8 February 2018|accessdate=11 February 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest 2019|2019]]\n| 1,170,000<ref name=\"Ratings 2019\"/>\n| 6.4%<ref name=\"Ratings 2019\">{{cite web|last=Granger|first=Andy|url=https://eurovoix.com/2019/02/09/united-kingdom-1-17-million-viewers-for-eurovision-you-decide/|title=United Kingdom: 1.17 Million Viewers for Eurovision: You Decide|website=eurovoix.com|publisher=Eurovoix|date=9 February 2019|accessdate=10 February 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[United Kingdom in the Eurovision Song Contest]]\n*[[UK Eurovision Song Contest entries discography]]\n\n== Notes and references ==\n===Notes===\n{{Notelist}}\n\n===References===\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Bbc.co.uk|id=eurovision/|title=Eurovision Song Contest}}\n*{{BBC programme|b01d73h5|title=Eurovision: Making Your Mind Up}}\n*{{BBC programme|b009hfkr|title=Eurovision: Your Decision}}\n*{{BBC programme|b00rfpgx|title=Eurovision: Your Country Needs You}}\n\n{{UK in Eurovision}}\n{{Eurovision Song Contest}}\n\n[[Category:1957 British television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2019 British television series endings]]\n[[Category:1950s British music television series]]\n[[Category:1960s British music television series]]\n[[Category:1970s British music television series]]\n[[Category:1